casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Walker, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Walker (1988), 39 Ohio St. 3d 606.]

(No. 87-1797 — Submitted October 4, 1988 — Decided November 9, 1988.) Lynn C. Slaby, prosecuting attorney, and Philip D. Bogdanojf, for appellee. D ’Andrea, Shumaker, Portman & Honeck and Thomas A. Shumaker, for appellant.

This cause is dismissed as having been improvidently allowed, but by so doing this court does not accept the reasoning of the opinion of the court of appeals.

Sweeney, Locher, Holmes and Douglas, JJ., concur. Moyer, C.J., Wright and H. Brown, JJ., dissent.
